<subSubSection id="0DFA65634A7AE00BFF0CFC90FB69FC81" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="455F36E84A7AE00BFF0CFC90FB69FC81" blockId="22.[151,1436,780,879]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="7794EAFA4A7AE00BFF0CFC90FEA4FCC8" bold="true" box="[151,260,780,806]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks</emphasis>
. No specimens of this species were examined. 
<bibRefCitation id="21714B194A7AE00BFC82FC90FC62FCC8" author="Nielson, M. W." box="[793,962,780,806]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="445 - 475" refId="ref38693" refString="Nielson, M. W. (1991) New Oriental leafhoppers in the tribe Coelidiini with a revised key to the species (Homoptera: Cicadellidae: Coelidiinae). Entomologica Scandinavica, 21, 445 - 475. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00355" type="journal article" year="1991">Nielson (1991)</bibRefCitation>
adequately redescribed and illustrated the species based on specimens collected from 
<collectingRegion id="8724F80A4A7AE00BFDE2FCACFD69FCA4" box="[633,713,816,842]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Assam</collectingRegion>
. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="82E04D6B4A7AE00BFC70FCADFBC9FCA4" baseAuthorityName="Distant" box="[1003,1129,816,843]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Olidiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perculta">
<emphasis id="7794EAFA4A7AE00BFC70FCADFBC9FCA4" box="[1003,1129,816,843]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">O. perculta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having a long caudoventral process of the pygofer (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A7AE00BFDA3FCC8FD39FC81" box="[568,665,851,879]" captionStart="FIGURES 35" captionStartId="70.[151,264,1771,1796]" captionTargetBox="[204,1364,191,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[189,1399,181,1751]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURES 35 A–T. Species of Olidiana Mckamey, male genitalia. A–D. O. pectita (Distant): E–H. O. peniculata (Nielson); I–L. O. perbrevis (Nielson); M–P. O. praetexta (Distant); Q–T. O. sparsispinulata (Nielson). Modified and reproduced from Nielson 1982 (Figs. A–H, M–T) and Nielson 1991 (Figs. I–L)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366614/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Fig. 
<date id="315E10284A7AE00BFDF7FCCFFD39FC81" box="[620,665,851,879]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1935-01">35 I</date>
</figureCitation>
) and short dentate aedeagal spine (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A7AE00BFBB9FCC8FBDEFC80" box="[1058,1150,851,878]" captionStart="FIGURES 35" captionStartId="70.[151,264,1771,1796]" captionTargetBox="[204,1364,191,1706]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[189,1399,181,1751]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURES 35 A–T. Species of Olidiana Mckamey, male genitalia. A–D. O. pectita (Distant): E–H. O. peniculata (Nielson); I–L. O. perbrevis (Nielson); M–P. O. praetexta (Distant); Q–T. O. sparsispinulata (Nielson). Modified and reproduced from Nielson 1982 (Figs. A–H, M–T) and Nielson 1991 (Figs. I–L)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366614/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs. 35</figureCitation>
K–L).
</paragraph>
